reviews.review: loved it from start to finish

i was excited to see this film, but as it drug on, I was eager for it to be over. When the troops road out of a troop carrier on horses on to the wing of a flying battle cruiser that was the tipping point for me. I mean what was the purpose of that? Physics aside, there were no enemy troops on the outside of the cruiser for them to fight. And then there was the kiss at the end. Uh no.

I was very sceptical going into this film. I thought there was no way that I would like episode nine given what had happened in 8, but JJ did a great job with what he had going into the film. I enjoyed it!
I liked the fact most of the third trilogy questions were answered. To me, this was a well directed film that I found fast paced and want to see again! I am sure there is more to understand.
Great effects, Best SoundTrack, and Kept me Entertained...!
I thoroughly enjoyed it. It made up for a lot of flaws of the previous two movies in the trilogy. There weren't many issues with the movie.

Good movie, especially for those of us who have seen this grow from A new hope in 1977. I think my only complaint is that you almost have to keep up with EVERYTHING star wars (cartoons, books, comic books, and movies) to fully understand everything that's going on and accept what the characters are doing. Gets to be a bit much. Maybe I'll go back and fill in the blanks. Could be fun.
It is action packed entertainment, but some of the story lines and decisions came across more as ‘winging it’ as opposed to thoroughly thought out.

As expected, the action and special effects were incredible.
A woman as the lead protagonist for a change was great to see and she pulls if off very nicely. My objection lies with her supporting actors, I thought they were totally drab, weak, and lacking in stage presence,  In the end, you really couldn't care less what happened to them, they never won you over, (that's a big no-no) the lackluster reunion at the end had me thinking: "who cares?"
For a movie of this magnitude, I'm quite surprised at the casting. What were you thinking???
I'm being generous giving it 3 stars.

Unpopular opinion - this was my favorite SW movie ever. Sure, there's a lot of huge plot holes in it and and a lot of cringe. So what? It's a movie about space monks fighting with light sabers and laser. Get over it and appreciate this movie for what is it - a film with incredible visuals, great action, best fighting scenes in the entire franchise and overall high quality production.
